Program: Outlook
Title: Life After the Iran-Iraq War
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbrqj
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
The long term human cost of the Iran-Iraq War as POWs struggle with adapting to freedom and repatriation. Also, Iraqi musician Naseer Shamma on playing the oud. Consumer responsibility and corporate ethics. A teacher recalls her memorable pupil, Mary McAleese, who became President of Ireland.